Region A
	•	EC2 Instance: Amazon Linux or Ubuntu
	•	Instance Type: t2.micro or t3.micro
	•	Network: Default VPC
	•	Storage:
	•	Root Volume (default)
	•	Extra EBS Volume (10–20 GB, gp3)

Snapshot
	•	Must be created from the extra EBS volume
	•	Must be copyable across regions
	•	Tags must identify source region and purpose

Region B
	•	Snapshot copy must exist
	•	New EBS volume must be created from the snapshot copy
	•	New EC2 instance must be launched in the same AZ as the new volume
	•	Volume must be attached as a secondary data volume